entry.title: Arthropodium fimbriatum
entry.content: Multiple flowers per node; most commonly single, unbranched flowering stem; buds and fruit commonly pendent.

entry.title: Rytidosperma erianthum
entry.content: Not dissimilar to Rytidosperma geniculatum, although R. erianthum is generally taller with larger head of inflorescence; hairs in distinct rows on lemma; not geniculate near base of flowering stem.

entry.title: Acacia farinosa
entry.content: An example of an atypical habit and habitat for this species occurring within a restricted distribution. Plants in this population are very low, rounded shrubs and often prostrate. Occurring predominately within Grey Box woodland.
